Location: Phase 3.1 and Phase 3.2 sub-phase labeling in results
Type: Structural
Severity: Minor
Description: The methodology labels sub-phases as "Dynamic Provisioning" and "Optimized Provisioning." The results section uses "Phase 3.1" and "Phase 3.2" inconsistently with these labels. The introduction to Phase 3 results says "Phase 3.1 implemented dynamic provisioning" and "Phase 3.2 employed optimized provisioning," establishing the equivalence. However, throughout the results discussion, the paper alternates between these naming conventions without consistent cross-reference. Table 3 uses "Phase 3.1" and "Phase 3.2" as column headers. The text sometimes says "optimized" and sometimes "Phase 3.2." Standardize to one naming convention throughout.
